Interface AnimationViewCV.OnTouchListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnimationUtilsCV.OnTouchListener_Relocation
    Enclosing class:
    AnimationViewCV

    public static interface AnimationViewCV.OnTouchListener
    Interface for Listeners that can be registered with an AnimationViewCV object and that will be called when a touch event occurs on this object.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      Header of a callback method that is called automatically when a touch event occurs on the view where the OnTouchListener is registered.

    • Method Detail

      • onTouch

        boolean onTouch(AnimationViewCV view,
                AnimatedGuiObjectCV guiobject,
                android.view.MotionEvent event)
        Header of a callback method that is called automatically when a touch event occurs on the view where the OnTouchListener is registered. Implement this method for a specific reaction on the event. NB: If a gesture detector is registered, its onTouchEvent() method will be called by the given onTouchEvent() method of this view. Hence, do not call the gesture detector's method here!
        Parameters:
        view -
        guiobject - Gui object that has been touched (null if no object was touched)
        event - The motion event
        Returns:
        true if the event was handled, false otherwise
